Thanks for all the feedback. I'm working through updating the the first
draft, and will drop root server discussion and will do some more diligence
at living in our modern dnssec world.

Injection of records, as in the case of China, does seem to be one of the
major attacks that the protocol has historically (and in practice
continues) to be vulnerable to; despite being mitigated by DNSSEC.  I'd be
interested in input in how that might be most effectively framed. Andrew
seems to suggest the injection section is hard to justify from the
protocol, and hurts the argument. Is there consensus that it should be
dropped?

--Will


