 a message of 41 lines which said:

> https://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-varon-hrpc-methodology-01

The draft says "The second form occurs through the use of deep packet
inspection, where all DNS protocol messages are inspected by the
network, and objectionable content is distorted, as in [turkey]." But
the article it references never mentions in-network DPI. As far as I
know, in Turkey, it was always through lying resolvers that censorship
was implemented.

Also "The DNS system is organized around a set of independently
operated 'Root Servers' run by organizations around the web" Are we
talking of the Internet or the Web? Also, the DNS is certainly not
organized around the root servers.


